<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued February 17 at 11:55AM EST until February 18 at 3:00AM EST by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM EST
FRIDAY...
* WHAT...Snow.  Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6 inches.
* WHERE...Lapeer, Sanilac, Shiawassee and Genesee Counties.
* WHEN...Until 3 AM EST Friday.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions will impact the evening commute.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Temperatures around 30 degrees has lead to
some icy surfaces with patchy freezing drizzle and residual
moisture from last night`s rain. Snow is not expected to develop
until very late today, with snow occuring throughout the evening
and then tapering off around or shortly after midnight.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.</instruction>
